qas.question: Who negotiated the agreement that Burma would be free from forgien rule ?
What is the name of the agreement that guarantee Burma's freedom from foreign rule ?
What leaders were present during the negotiations made for freedom of the Burmese people?

answers.text: Aung Zan Wai, Pe Khin, Bo Hmu Aung, Sir Maung Gyi, Dr. Sein Mya Maung, Myoma U Than Kywe

qas.question: What position did Aung San hold in the Burmese government?

answers.text: Deputy Chairman of the Executive Council of Myanmar

qas.question: When did and how did Aung San pass away ?

answers.text: July 1947, political rivals assassinated Aung San

context: Following World War II, <a0_0>Aung San<a0_0/> negotiated <a1_0>the Panglong Agreement<a1_0/> with ethnic leaders that guaranteed the independence of Myanmar as a unified state. <a2_0>Aung Zan Wai, Pe Khin, Bo Hmu Aung, Sir Maung Gyi, Dr. Sein Mya Maung, Myoma U Than Kywe<a2_0/> were among the negotiators of the historical Panglong Conference negotiated with Bamar leader General Aung San and other ethnic leaders in 1947. In 1947, Aung San became <a3_0>Deputy Chairman of the Executive Council of Myanmar<a3_0/>, a transitional government. But in <a4_0>July 1947, political rivals assassinated Aung San<a4_0/> and several cabinet members.
